He had been in self-quarantine at home. He was transferred to hospital on Monday night on the advice of his doctor, the statement said. Nxesi is the second Cabinet Minister to be hospitalised. Energy Minister Gwede Mantashe was admitted to hospital on Monday after testing positive for Covid-19. South Africa has the highest number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in Africa. About 360 000 cases have been reported with just over 5000 deaths. --BBC--